<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The Hyperion is widely regarded as the best ship in the <a href="/index.php/M6%2B" title="M6+">M6+</a> class. Fast, powerful, well defended and with a quick turn rate for its class, it is capable of taking a fight to any opponent, from <a href="/index.php/M5" title="M5">scouts</a> to <a href="/index.php/M2" title="M2">destroyers</a>. On top of its impressive combat capabilities, it is the only corvette in the <a href="/index.php/X-universe" title="X-universe">X-universe</a> to have the function to dock and launch two <a href="/index.php/Category:Fighters" title="Category:Fighters">fighter class</a> ships - this gives this ship the versitility to operate in many situations. However, it is not available to buy, and must be <a href="/index.php/Bigship_Boarding" title="Bigship Boarding" class="mw-redirect"><i>acquired</i></a> by other means.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>The Hyperion was first introduced as a prototype M7 class yacht for the <a href="/index.php/Paranid" title="Paranid">Paranid</a> where it was significantly larger and more powerful. Its classification has changed over time to a cheaper and more compact M6, but remains a rather unique vessel, even after it started to be produced in larger numbers.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<p>The Hyperion's sleek lines demonstrate typical Paranid design. It has a small profile from both forward and the side and the upper profile is not particularly large either.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>The Hyperion has eight main guns, two side turrets that can fire forwards as well as having a huge angular range, and two rear three gun mount turrets. It can be equipped with all of the common corvette weapons in the main battery; <a href="/index.php/High_Energy_Plasma_Thrower" title="High Energy Plasma Thrower">HEPT</a>, <a href="/index.php/Concussion_Impulse_Generator" title="Concussion Impulse Generator">CIG</a>, <a href="/index.php/Energy_Bolt_Chaingun" title="Energy Bolt Chaingun">EBC</a>, <a href="/index.php/Pulsed_Beam_Emitter" title="Pulsed Beam Emitter">PBE</a>, <a href="/index.php/Ion_Shard_Railgun" title="Ion Shard Railgun">ISR</a> and <a href="/index.php/Plasma_Burst_Generator" title="Plasma Burst Generator">PBG</a> as well as the Paranid's own flak weapon, the <a href="/index.php/Fragmentation_Bomb_Launcher" title="Fragmentation Bomb Launcher">Fragmentation Bomb Launcher</a>. As such, it can be equipped with specialist weapons for every combat role. 
</p><p>Choice in the forward turrets is more restricted, with only HEPT, EBC and FBL as options unless the more ubiquitous <a href="/index.php/Particle_Accelerator_Cannon" title="Particle Accelerator Cannon">PAC</a>, which can be mounted in all slots and is an old but very effective weapon, is used.
</p><p>The rear turrets are most restricted of all; only FBL and PAC can be mounted here.
</p><p>Although it does not mount any heavy guns, it is the only <a href="/index.php/Commonwealth" title="Commonwealth">Commonwealth</a> vessel capable of launching the immensely potent <a href="/index.php/Wraith_Missile" title="Wraith Missile">Wraith Missile</a> at a target, and also the only one capable of matching the Wraith's maximum speed (170 m/s), so that many can be launched on top of the others if the target is far enough. This overwhelms any defenses.
</p><p>The Hyperion's shields are among the strongest of all M6s at 1GJ, allowing it to take a massive amount of punishment before succumbing.
</p>
